						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab (A-38 right side) in the Museum.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōvidēva—A.D. 1173.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">[7]th</hi> regnal year of <hi rend="bold">Rāyamurāri Sōmēśvara, Vijaya, Pushya ba. 4, Tuesday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkramaṇa,</hi> corresponding regularly to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1173, December 25, Tuesday.</hi> It records a grant of land and house sites made by <hi rend="bold">Ghaṭeyama-Sāhaṇi</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Śrīdharabhaṭṭa</hi> and others as the <hi rend="italic">brahmapuri</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Mūlasthānadēva.</hi></p>						

